1
00:00:04,130 --> 00:00:05,548
You promised me that you wouldn't leave.

2
00:00:10,636 --> 00:00:12,346
Just make sure you win!

3
00:00:26,402 --> 00:00:28,821
He'll be the lead investigator
on this case.

4
00:00:28,904 --> 00:00:31,782
He'll also be the acting chief
until I have a replacement.

5
00:00:31,866 --> 00:00:33,325
Jackie…

6
00:00:34,243 --> 00:00:37,371
You don't believe
Ms. Ignacio took her own life?

7
00:00:37,455 --> 00:00:39,498
Her phone is missing.

8
00:00:39,582 --> 00:00:41,542
She had a date with someone we don't know.

9
00:00:41,625 --> 00:00:43,794
Shouldn't we be looking for him?

10
00:00:43,878 --> 00:00:47,214
Ms. Ignacio had
a tutorial session yesterday.

11
00:00:47,298 --> 00:00:48,924
The student's name is Eli.

12
00:00:49,008 --> 00:00:51,093
We might have to find a new tutor for Eli.

13
00:00:51,177 --> 00:00:54,054
Aren't you going to accept the promotion?
What about Eli?

14
00:00:54,138 --> 00:00:57,808
No matter how busy I am,
my family is my top priority.

15
00:00:57,892 --> 00:00:58,726
I'm Manu Cortez,

16
00:00:58,809 --> 00:01:01,061
the lead investigator
in Ms. Ignacio's case.

17
00:01:01,145 --> 00:01:03,439
When was the last time
you saw Ms. Ignacio?

18
00:01:10,321 --> 00:01:11,363
Almost done, son.

19
00:01:16,118 --> 00:01:17,286
Pia?

20
00:01:18,204 --> 00:01:19,789
Are you guys okay, Matteo?

21
00:01:20,623 --> 00:01:22,041
Why is there so much smoke?

22
00:01:22,124 --> 00:01:23,000
Anton!

23
00:01:25,961 --> 00:01:29,632
-What's going on?
-Papa's special breakfast!

24
00:01:31,425 --> 00:01:33,302
Oh, my goodness.

25
00:01:36,138 --> 00:01:37,348
What's this?

26
00:01:40,976 --> 00:01:42,978
Dig in, kids. Go ahead.

27
00:01:43,562 --> 00:01:45,815
-Dig in.
-Ouch.

28
00:01:46,816 --> 00:01:49,693
-What happened? He kicked?
-It's nothing. Just a small kick.

29
00:01:49,777 --> 00:01:50,736
Eli?

30
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:54,949
I think Eli's just thanking you
for the effort.

31
00:01:57,618 --> 00:02:01,622
Don't worry. When you come out,
your dad will be a master chef.

32
00:02:01,705 --> 00:02:03,582
I'll prepare breakfast every day.

33
00:02:04,375 --> 00:02:07,670
Jeez, Pa. Eli might never come out now.

34
00:02:08,963 --> 00:02:12,675
Don't say that.
He might hear you and get scared.

35
00:04:51,125 --> 00:04:52,501
She also has multiple scratches.

36
00:04:52,584 --> 00:04:55,671
She likely skidded down
before falling off.

37
00:04:55,754 --> 00:04:58,257
Looks like she has
extensive fractures of the ribs,

38
00:04:58,340 --> 00:05:00,843
pelvis, and lower extremities.

39
00:05:07,057 --> 00:05:09,768
Cortez, who ordered the autopsy?

40
00:05:11,687 --> 00:05:14,314
It was requested by her family, sir.

41
00:05:14,815 --> 00:05:16,191
Is there a problem?

42
00:05:22,823 --> 00:05:24,033
Can I have that?

43
00:05:24,116 --> 00:05:27,161
-Hey, I'm still eating that.
-I thought you were done.

44
00:05:38,797 --> 00:05:39,923
Pa, I'll drive.

45
00:05:40,007 --> 00:05:42,843
No, I'll drive. Maybe next time.

46
00:05:42,926 --> 00:05:45,137
-I can do it.
-Next time.

47
00:05:54,605 --> 00:05:57,524
I'm just one call away.

48
00:06:01,278 --> 00:06:05,824
Just text a period,
and Papa or I will come running.

49
00:06:07,159 --> 00:06:09,453
Pa, maybe Eli should stay home.

50
00:06:09,536 --> 00:06:12,498
-I can watch over him.
-You wish.

51
00:06:14,041 --> 00:06:15,250
Eli.

52
00:06:16,210 --> 00:06:18,295
Do you want to stay home?

53
00:06:19,922 --> 00:06:21,632
No, no, no.

54
00:06:21,715 --> 00:06:24,259
We're all leaving together.

55
00:06:24,343 --> 00:06:28,806
And we're all coming home together.

56
00:06:33,477 --> 00:06:34,603
That's right.

57
00:06:34,686 --> 00:06:38,398
Nobody gets left behind.

58
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:52,204
The mayor's getting impatient.

59
00:06:52,287 --> 00:06:53,997
It won't be long now, Chief.

60
00:06:54,665 --> 00:06:55,874
Cortez.

61
00:06:58,127 --> 00:07:02,381
We've only met with one member
of her family, her cousin.

62
00:07:02,464 --> 00:07:04,800
I've tracked down her psychiatrist.

63
00:07:04,883 --> 00:07:09,054
And they both claimed that Sam Ignacio
did not exhibit suicidal tendencies.

64
00:07:09,138 --> 00:07:11,306
Is suicide still our angle?

65
00:07:11,390 --> 00:07:14,560
Do you have any other leads
in your investigation?

66
00:07:15,227 --> 00:07:17,354
Here's what you need to know, Cortez.

67
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:19,690
A lot of people are watching this case.

68
00:07:21,150 --> 00:07:24,027
But not all of them
are interested in the truth.

69
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:54,057
I know it's a strong offer,
but my family needs me right now.

70
00:07:54,683 --> 00:07:55,767
Especially Eli.

71
00:07:55,851 --> 00:07:59,396
I want to focus on my son.

72
00:08:00,272 --> 00:08:05,194
And as a mother, I can feel
that my son needs me right now.

73
00:08:17,372 --> 00:08:18,874
As his mother,

74
00:08:19,583 --> 00:08:22,211
you're the best person he can rely on now.

75
00:08:26,548 --> 00:08:31,678
I've heard what people
have been saying about Sam.

76
00:08:32,888 --> 00:08:36,600
Some say she committed suicide.

77
00:08:47,569 --> 00:08:51,448
You're a counselor and her friend.

78
00:08:52,532 --> 00:08:56,161
Was she going through something?

79
00:08:57,829 --> 00:09:00,749
That's why I refuse to believe it.

80
00:09:01,917 --> 00:09:06,338
There was so much
that Sam still wanted to do in life.

81
00:09:15,973 --> 00:09:17,474
Speaking of which, ma'am…

82
00:09:18,267 --> 00:09:20,435
I would like to volunteer.

83
00:09:21,645 --> 00:09:23,522
I would love to help out…

84
00:09:24,773 --> 00:09:26,775
at the memorial service for Sam.

85
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:31,780
It's the least I could do for her.

86
00:09:45,127 --> 00:09:48,547
Can you move these to the side?

87
00:09:54,636 --> 00:09:57,639
-Where are the big flowers?
-They're on the way, Anton.

88
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:02,019
Is it lopsided?
Put it there to keep this steady.

89
00:10:06,857 --> 00:10:09,776
We were planning
how to arrange the chapel.

90
00:10:10,277 --> 00:10:13,572
When he heard, he volunteered right away.

91
00:10:15,782 --> 00:10:18,410
Your family must have
been really close with Sam.

92
00:10:21,538 --> 00:10:25,500
-I brought more pictures of Sam.
-Are these from the office?

93
00:11:34,194 --> 00:11:35,779
Why did you come here?

94
00:11:36,571 --> 00:11:39,950
Who are you with?

95
00:12:49,311 --> 00:12:50,729
Jackie.

96
00:13:01,615 --> 00:13:07,287
We know that we are all very eager
to be with our dear Teacher Sam.

97
00:13:07,370 --> 00:13:12,125
But her remains won't be here today…

98
00:13:13,126 --> 00:13:15,754
because they're still being prepared

99
00:13:17,005 --> 00:13:20,383
after undergoing an autopsy.

100
00:13:25,263 --> 00:13:27,390
Is that why her body was broken all over?

101
00:13:27,474 --> 00:13:28,725
Maybe there was foul play.

102
00:13:30,268 --> 00:13:31,228
Could it be murder?

103
00:13:32,479 --> 00:13:34,564
-Maybe she was raped…
-Possibly.

104
00:13:35,357 --> 00:13:37,150
-And then killed.
-Guys, wait a minute.

105
00:13:37,234 --> 00:13:41,154
We shouldn't be like this.
Let's give Sam some respect.

106
00:13:41,238 --> 00:13:46,701
If you have questions,
I'm sure those can wait, right?

107
00:13:46,785 --> 00:13:48,703
But for now, please…

108
00:13:48,787 --> 00:13:51,540
Let's learn to be respectful.

109
00:13:52,123 --> 00:13:53,917
I'm begging you.

110
00:13:54,626 --> 00:13:59,256
We'll just make an announcement
when the viewing is ready.

111
00:13:59,339 --> 00:14:00,924
Thank you very much.

112
00:14:07,055 --> 00:14:09,474
Anton. You can leave now.

113
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:12,477
Eli, let's go.

114
00:14:12,561 --> 00:14:13,562
Come on.

115
00:14:27,993 --> 00:14:31,037
Eli. Rest?

116
00:14:44,009 --> 00:14:45,302
Mr. Carpio.

117
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:51,224
What do you need?

118
00:14:51,891 --> 00:14:53,518
I just wanted to check on you.

119
00:14:53,602 --> 00:14:55,604
I heard you're the ones
organizing the wake.

120
00:14:55,687 --> 00:14:57,981
She was our friend and co-worker.

121
00:15:02,402 --> 00:15:06,448
Come on. Let's go.

122
00:15:11,703 --> 00:15:13,371
Is there anything else you need?

123
00:15:13,997 --> 00:15:16,374
Actually, yes. You.

124
00:15:18,793 --> 00:15:20,629
I still have some questions for you.

125
00:15:27,010 --> 00:15:28,470
Pia, dear.

126
00:15:28,553 --> 00:15:30,138
You can head home first.
Look for your brother.

127
00:15:30,221 --> 00:15:31,097
Okay.

128
00:15:41,358 --> 00:15:43,026
Detective, let's talk over there.

129
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:52,285
-Matt.
-Pia.

130
00:15:52,369 --> 00:15:54,079
Why? Did something happen?

131
00:15:54,162 --> 00:15:56,498
Mama and Papa said
we could head home first.

132
00:15:57,248 --> 00:15:58,083
Okay. Come on.

133
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:07,258
Matt, are you avoiding me?

134
00:16:11,304 --> 00:16:12,263
Follow me, Jem.

135
00:16:16,267 --> 00:16:18,895
Mrs. Carpio, you don't have to stay here.

136
00:16:18,978 --> 00:16:20,939
I only need to talk to your husband.

137
00:16:21,022 --> 00:16:22,982
We were open to each other.

138
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:25,527
What is this about?

139
00:16:26,194 --> 00:16:27,487
Did you find anything--

140
00:16:27,570 --> 00:16:32,617
I mean, did you discover new information
about what really happened to Sam?

141
00:16:34,244 --> 00:16:36,955
You really don't believe
she committed suicide, do you?

142
00:16:38,748 --> 00:16:41,459
This is just based on
what I know about my friend.

143
00:16:42,460 --> 00:16:43,378
Wait, detective.

144
00:16:43,461 --> 00:16:45,964
I thought I was the only one
you wanted to talk to.

145
00:16:46,047 --> 00:16:47,924
Do we really need to do this right now?

146
00:16:48,007 --> 00:16:51,970
I can just drop by the station tomorrow.

147
00:16:52,929 --> 00:16:55,515
No. Let's do it right here, right now.

148
00:16:55,598 --> 00:16:58,601
I really need to know
what actually happened to my friend.

149
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:03,523
I'll just ask a few questions
since we're already here.

150
00:17:08,778 --> 00:17:11,740
Have you tried the Mexican restaurant
by the highway?

151
00:17:14,367 --> 00:17:15,785
Los Pollos.

152
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:20,957
I've heard of it, but…

153
00:17:21,583 --> 00:17:23,668
No, I haven't tried it yet.

154
00:17:25,128 --> 00:17:27,297
A week before Ms. Ignacio died,

155
00:17:28,006 --> 00:17:31,926
a guy grabbed her at the back
of the Los Pollos Restaurant

156
00:17:32,427 --> 00:17:33,928
and forcibly kissed her.

157
00:17:35,472 --> 00:17:39,058
The witness heard her call the guy's name.

158
00:17:40,268 --> 00:17:41,394
And the name was…

159
00:17:42,395 --> 00:17:43,313
Anton.

160
00:17:46,566 --> 00:17:49,068
Do you know anything
about this, Mr. Carpio?

161
00:17:53,448 --> 00:17:54,824
What are you doing?

162
00:17:56,117 --> 00:17:57,368
Can you not do this right now?

163
00:17:57,452 --> 00:17:59,412
There's a lot going on. Can we…

164
00:17:59,996 --> 00:18:01,623
Can we take a breather?

165
00:18:01,706 --> 00:18:04,959
I just don't understand
why you're still avoiding me.

166
00:18:05,502 --> 00:18:07,504
Teacher Sam is gone now. No one--

167
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:12,550
Hey, be careful with what you say.

168
00:18:12,634 --> 00:18:15,220
Don't ever mention that name again, okay?

169
00:18:21,768 --> 00:18:22,894
Besides…

170
00:18:23,937 --> 00:18:26,314
what matters is we don't have
a problem anymore, right?

171
00:18:29,651 --> 00:18:30,985
Right, Jem?

172
00:18:34,989 --> 00:18:36,115
Matt…

173
00:18:37,659 --> 00:18:39,410
Please don't leave me.

174
00:18:40,870 --> 00:18:42,664
Matt, I need you.

175
00:18:45,166 --> 00:18:46,584
We need you.

176
00:18:50,672 --> 00:18:53,633
Jem, hold on.
We already talked about this, right?

177
00:18:53,716 --> 00:18:56,302
You said you got rid of it, didn't you?

178
00:18:56,386 --> 00:18:58,763
Sorry, Matt, I lied.

179
00:19:00,014 --> 00:19:01,599
I didn't get rid of it.

180
00:19:02,725 --> 00:19:04,310
I couldn't do it.

181
00:19:08,481 --> 00:19:09,566
Matt…

182
00:19:10,483 --> 00:19:12,110
-Seriously, Jem?
-Matt…

183
00:19:14,696 --> 00:19:16,239
You're so stubborn, Jem.

184
00:19:27,917 --> 00:19:31,546
Whatever you're thinking,
that's not what happened.

185
00:19:33,131 --> 00:19:34,215
Yes, I was there.

186
00:19:35,008 --> 00:19:38,761
I just happened to see Sam.

187
00:19:38,845 --> 00:19:41,723
I approached her and said hello.

188
00:19:41,806 --> 00:19:46,144
Then she told me
she was waiting for someone.

189
00:19:46,769 --> 00:19:48,021
Yes, that's it.

190
00:19:48,855 --> 00:19:53,860
But I didn't grab her
or force a kiss on her.

191
00:19:58,323 --> 00:19:59,949
I'm very happy with my wife.

192
00:20:01,701 --> 00:20:04,245
Okay. Just relax.

193
00:20:07,540 --> 00:20:09,375
But what were you doing there?

194
00:20:10,585 --> 00:20:12,128
Los Pollos is out of town.

195
00:20:18,593 --> 00:20:21,304
To be honest, yes, I went there.

196
00:20:23,890 --> 00:20:27,685
I was looking for a new restaurant
where I could take my wife

197
00:20:27,769 --> 00:20:29,979
because we haven't gone
on a date in a long time.

198
00:20:30,563 --> 00:20:32,148
When I checked the reviews,
it looked great.

199
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:35,777
But when I went there myself,
it wasn't that good, so…

200
00:20:36,778 --> 00:20:40,865
If I check the CCTV footage,
is it going to match your story?

201
00:20:44,077 --> 00:20:48,957
Then why don't you do that
instead of wasting your time on us here?

202
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:51,834
Right?

203
00:20:53,711 --> 00:20:55,546
You're making a serious accusation.

204
00:20:56,339 --> 00:20:58,841
You're implying
that I committed sexual assault.

205
00:20:58,925 --> 00:21:02,553
Maybe you should focus
your time on the real suspect.

206
00:21:03,972 --> 00:21:07,517
Okay, thank you.
That's all I wanted to ask.

207
00:21:09,852 --> 00:21:13,606
I hope this doesn't happen again.
Let's not waste each other's time.

208
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:43,720
Please turn left at that corner.

209
00:21:43,803 --> 00:21:44,846
Alright, sir.

210
00:22:08,453 --> 00:22:09,537
Thanks.

211
00:22:17,003 --> 00:22:18,337
You really won't talk to me?

212
00:22:18,421 --> 00:22:21,924
-You want us to face the kids like this?
-Anton, I just don't understand.

213
00:22:22,717 --> 00:22:25,845
How long were you planning
to hide that you met with Sam?

214
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:30,767
I just said hello.
I didn't think I had to tell you.

215
00:22:31,559 --> 00:22:34,145
Besides, I came there in secret, remember?

216
00:22:34,228 --> 00:22:37,565
Really? Was that all?
You didn't talk about anything else there?

217
00:22:39,734 --> 00:22:40,860
Nothing.

218
00:22:40,943 --> 00:22:42,528
I just said hello, Jackie.

219
00:22:48,618 --> 00:22:51,537
Don't tell me you believe
what that detective said.

220
00:22:54,582 --> 00:22:55,666
Come on, Jackie.

221
00:22:56,834 --> 00:22:59,003
He's just looking for someone
to pin the crime on

222
00:22:59,087 --> 00:23:01,798
because he's a newbie from the city,

223
00:23:02,465 --> 00:23:04,133
who wants to make a name here.

224
00:23:04,717 --> 00:23:08,054
So, what? The witness just made it all up?

225
00:23:08,721 --> 00:23:10,556
Is that what you're trying to say?

226
00:23:11,182 --> 00:23:14,769
But why? Why would he make up a story?

227
00:23:14,852 --> 00:23:17,146
-I don't know.
-Seriously…

228
00:23:25,113 --> 00:23:27,156
Where are Matt and Pia?

229
00:23:27,865 --> 00:23:29,117
I don't know.

230
00:23:58,312 --> 00:24:03,609
We called him in for questioning
to find out if he was telling the truth.

231
00:24:04,318 --> 00:24:06,112
Why would he lie?

232
00:24:06,696 --> 00:24:09,991
We asked around, did a background check,

233
00:24:10,575 --> 00:24:12,702
and found out that he had a record.

234
00:24:13,995 --> 00:24:15,204
Talk to him.

235
00:24:25,798 --> 00:24:28,259
Ma'am, I'm telling the truth.

236
00:24:28,342 --> 00:24:34,056
Whatever record I had in the past,
it's already been settled.

237
00:24:34,140 --> 00:24:36,017
Wait, what record?

238
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:38,186
It's not a criminal record.

239
00:24:38,269 --> 00:24:41,230
Well, his memory is just not that sharp.

240
00:24:41,314 --> 00:24:43,399
Ma'am, I may not have a good memory, but…

241
00:24:44,108 --> 00:24:45,443
I'm not a liar.

242
00:24:47,069 --> 00:24:48,529
Here's my question for you.

243
00:24:48,613 --> 00:24:52,116
Are you sure the name Sam Ignacio said
was really "Anton"?

244
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:53,659
Yes, sir.

245
00:24:53,743 --> 00:24:58,372
Are you sure he was the one
who followed Ms. Ignacio to the back…

246
00:24:58,456 --> 00:25:01,751
then grabbed her and forced a kiss on her?

247
00:25:10,218 --> 00:25:12,470
But I saw them…

248
00:25:12,553 --> 00:25:14,847
heading out together.

249
00:25:16,557 --> 00:25:18,100
So, in other words…

250
00:25:19,769 --> 00:25:22,688
you didn't see Anton
talking to Sam Ignacio

251
00:25:22,772 --> 00:25:24,523
at the back of the restaurant?

252
00:25:38,955 --> 00:25:41,123
-Anton!
-Hey, Hans, come on.

253
00:25:47,380 --> 00:25:48,589
No, I didn't.

254
00:26:28,963 --> 00:26:32,425
What happened? Did you help the policeman?

255
00:26:33,426 --> 00:26:36,304
Yes, we did.

256
00:26:40,391 --> 00:26:43,936
Have they found out
what happened to Teacher Sam?

257
00:26:45,187 --> 00:26:47,231
Is what they're saying true?

258
00:26:49,817 --> 00:26:52,903
What are they saying?

259
00:27:01,287 --> 00:27:03,539
I don't know, Pia. I don't know.

260
00:27:05,082 --> 00:27:06,250
Okay.

261
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:11,088
Matteo.

262
00:27:12,423 --> 00:27:15,051
Are you okay? Is there a problem?

263
00:27:23,059 --> 00:27:24,060
No, Ma.

264
00:27:24,769 --> 00:27:25,686
I'm fine.

265
00:27:26,937 --> 00:27:27,772
What about Jem?

266
00:27:33,569 --> 00:27:34,737
She's okay.

267
00:27:35,988 --> 00:27:38,824
Whatever it is, you can tell me, okay?

268
00:27:41,118 --> 00:27:42,370
When you're ready.

269
00:28:03,766 --> 00:28:06,769
Are you sure you're not going to tell me
who did that to you?

270
00:28:07,269 --> 00:28:08,479
No need.

271
00:28:09,688 --> 00:28:11,690
I'm not going to stay here long anyway.

272
00:28:13,901 --> 00:28:15,277
You're not leaving.

273
00:28:15,861 --> 00:28:19,365
As I said, we're staying here.

274
00:28:20,408 --> 00:28:23,119
You must've crossed someone powerful
to get thrown out here.

275
00:28:23,202 --> 00:28:24,787
Now, I'm stuck here too.

276
00:28:25,746 --> 00:28:27,415
You'll get used to this place, eventually.

277
00:28:32,086 --> 00:28:33,754
I had a life there.

278
00:28:35,256 --> 00:28:37,716
Why do I have to suffer
for your stubbornness too?

279
00:28:45,391 --> 00:28:48,686
-I just did what I had to do.
-"What you had to do"?

280
00:28:49,311 --> 00:28:51,313
Or you just always want to be
the one who's right?

281
00:29:40,613 --> 00:29:42,448
Are you okay?

282
00:29:53,792 --> 00:29:55,669
I know you're sad.

283
00:29:55,753 --> 00:29:59,131
I know you're sad
because you miss Teacher Sam.

284
00:29:59,215 --> 00:30:04,136
And that's okay. We miss her too.

285
00:30:22,696 --> 00:30:27,493
Mama will spend more time with you.

286
00:30:27,576 --> 00:30:32,748
Because from now on, I will be your tutor.

287
00:30:32,831 --> 00:30:34,333
Is that okay?

288
00:31:03,445 --> 00:31:05,364
I'm here. Hurry up.

289
00:31:05,447 --> 00:31:07,491
-Kyle.
-Where?

290
00:31:07,575 --> 00:31:08,909
Where are you?

291
00:31:10,202 --> 00:31:11,829
Stupid-- No--

292
00:31:11,912 --> 00:31:13,789
Okay. I'm on my way.

293
00:31:18,377 --> 00:31:20,129
You're really screwed, man.

294
00:31:21,630 --> 00:31:22,965
You're such a noob.

295
00:31:23,048 --> 00:31:24,466
What?

296
00:31:34,268 --> 00:31:35,769
Matt, I need you.

297
00:31:36,729 --> 00:31:38,230
We need you.

298
00:31:40,024 --> 00:31:42,651
Sorry, Matt, I lied.

299
00:31:42,735 --> 00:31:45,654
I didn't get rid of it. I couldn't do it.

300
00:32:42,586 --> 00:32:44,630
Sam Ignacio
Matteo will pick up Eli later.

301
00:33:10,531 --> 00:33:12,157
I'll just go on a quick run.

302
00:33:35,681 --> 00:33:36,849
Wow, nice and clean.

303
00:33:58,162 --> 00:34:00,956
-So…
-We had no classes last weekend, right?

304
00:34:01,039 --> 00:34:03,250
I needed to work. You know that…

305
00:34:16,096 --> 00:34:19,308
I saw the way you were with her, Anton.

306
00:34:23,187 --> 00:34:26,064
Whatever we had, I've ended it, Jackie.

307
00:34:26,148 --> 00:34:28,859
You only ended it because you got caught!

308
00:34:33,030 --> 00:34:34,948
I chose you, Jackie.

309
00:34:35,032 --> 00:34:36,492
I'm here.

310
00:34:37,242 --> 00:34:39,620
I'm staying with you
because I love you, Jackie.

311
00:34:42,206 --> 00:34:45,250
You're staying
because it's convenient for you.

312
00:34:46,460 --> 00:34:47,836
Jackie…

313
00:34:48,337 --> 00:34:50,547
When I get back, I want you gone.

314
00:34:52,883 --> 00:34:54,092
Jackie…

315
00:34:54,927 --> 00:34:56,094
Jackie, please.

316
00:34:56,178 --> 00:34:57,387
Jackie…

317
00:34:58,222 --> 00:35:00,224
Jackie, please…

318
00:35:05,312 --> 00:35:06,438
Jackie…

319
00:35:27,835 --> 00:35:30,087
Jackie, I'm sorry…

320
00:35:31,463 --> 00:35:34,049
Jackie, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

321
00:35:50,816 --> 00:35:53,902
You're shaking.

322
00:36:01,660 --> 00:36:05,831
Sorry.

323
00:36:07,332 --> 00:36:09,668
Are you okay?

324
00:36:12,170 --> 00:36:17,426
Don't worry.

325
00:36:28,770 --> 00:36:29,938
Jackie.

326
00:36:30,022 --> 00:36:31,857
Sam is here.

327
00:37:34,628 --> 00:37:35,754
Sam…

328
00:38:04,408 --> 00:38:05,701
You can give these out.

329
00:38:07,452 --> 00:38:09,162
Jackie.

330
00:38:11,206 --> 00:38:12,958
Thank you very much.

331
00:38:13,041 --> 00:38:15,419
I heard that you and Sam were very close.

332
00:38:18,422 --> 00:38:19,840
Don't mention it.

333
00:38:34,938 --> 00:38:38,275
Sorry, but a lot of people noticed

334
00:38:38,358 --> 00:38:41,570
that the detective talked
to you here yesterday.

335
00:38:42,279 --> 00:38:46,742
I don't know,
but they said Anton got angry.

336
00:38:48,493 --> 00:38:51,496
Now, there are these rumors going around.

337
00:38:51,580 --> 00:38:53,957
Some are even saying
Anton might be involved.

338
00:38:55,625 --> 00:38:56,877
He's not.

339
00:38:58,545 --> 00:39:00,756
The detective just asked us

340
00:39:01,757 --> 00:39:06,762
if we noticed anything unusual about Sam.

341
00:39:06,845 --> 00:39:07,971
That's all.

342
00:39:08,555 --> 00:39:10,849
People really do love to imagine things.

343
00:39:34,414 --> 00:39:36,208
Are you Jackie?

344
00:39:37,375 --> 00:39:40,629
I'm Shiela, Sam's cousin.

345
00:39:41,421 --> 00:39:43,006
She adored your son.

346
00:39:44,257 --> 00:39:45,717
Eli, right?

347
00:39:47,886 --> 00:39:50,388
She said she'd miss him.

348
00:39:50,889 --> 00:39:52,724
She didn't want to leave him.

349
00:39:54,684 --> 00:39:56,269
Have a seat first, Shiela.

350
00:39:57,771 --> 00:39:58,814
Thank you.

351
00:41:10,468 --> 00:41:11,553
Eli's here.

352
00:41:26,735 --> 00:41:27,611
Anton.

353
00:41:27,694 --> 00:41:30,071
I asked him several times.
He said he's fine.

354
00:41:37,537 --> 00:41:40,582
For Teacher Sam.

355
00:41:40,665 --> 00:41:44,252
Can we put it there?

356
00:41:45,337 --> 00:41:46,880
Of course.

357
00:41:46,963 --> 00:41:52,761
Teacher Sam would've been so proud.

358
00:45:50,206 --> 00:45:51,040
Let go!

359
00:46:11,603 --> 00:46:12,770
Anton?

360
00:46:15,148 --> 00:46:16,858
Anton, is that you?

361
00:46:18,401 --> 00:46:19,402
Anton?

362
00:46:27,243 --> 00:46:28,661
Anton?

363
00:46:35,627 --> 00:46:37,003
Anton, is that you?

364
00:46:50,934 --> 00:46:52,644
What are you doing here?

365
00:47:26,094 --> 00:47:28,221
I was only letting out my frustrations.

366
00:47:28,304 --> 00:47:31,057
Why would people think
I had a hand in her death?

367
00:47:31,140 --> 00:47:34,060
What, do they think
Sam and I had an affair?

368
00:47:34,143 --> 00:47:35,520
Well, did you?

369
00:47:38,398 --> 00:47:41,359
Did you notice anything strange?

370
00:47:41,442 --> 00:47:43,861
Did she seem tired or stressed?
Any sign she was harassed?

371
00:47:43,945 --> 00:47:46,948
Was Ms. Ignacio paid to do
something she didn't want to?

372
00:47:47,031 --> 00:47:49,534
Do you really have to tarnish
my friend's memory?

373
00:47:49,617 --> 00:47:51,703
How well did you know your friend?

374
00:47:52,537 --> 00:47:55,832
I refuse to believe
that Sam gave up on life.

375
00:47:55,915 --> 00:47:59,085
If you're one of the people
she once helped,

376
00:47:59,168 --> 00:48:01,337
please don't accept the assumption

377
00:48:01,421 --> 00:48:04,716
that she chose to end her story
by giving up.
